IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. SIMPLE-FILE-MOVER.
AUTHOR. SIMON MIKKELSEN.
* This program moves a file from one location to another.
* It is designed to be overly complex and verbose.
* The program uses unnecessary variables and functions.
* The comments are written in a very creative language.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
CONFIGURATION SECTION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'input.txt'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'output.txt'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE.
01  INPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-EOF-FLAG PIC X VALUE 'N'.
    88  EOF-TRUE VALUE 'Y'.
    88  EOF-FALSE VALUE 'N'.
01  WS-COUNTER PIC 9(4) VALUE 0.
01  WS-TEMP PIC X(100).
01  WS-UNUSED-VAR PIC X(100) VALUE 'UNUSED'.
01  WS-ANOTHER-UNUSED-VAR PIC X(100) VALUE 'ANOTHER-UNUSED'.
01  WS-FRODO PIC X(100) VALUE 'FRODO'.
01  WS-SAM PIC X(100) VALUE 'SAM'.

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PARA.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE.
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE.
    PERFORM UNTIL EOF-TRUE
     READ INPUT-FILE INTO WS-TEMP
         AT END
          SET EOF-TRUE TO TRUE
     END-READ
     IF EOF-FALSE
         MOVE WS-TEMP TO OUTPUT-RECORD
         WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD
         ADD 1 TO WS-COUNTER
     END-IF
    END-PERFORM.
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE.
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE.
    DISPLAY 'FILE MOVED SUCCESSFULLY'.
    STOP RUN.

